cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a competitive bidding system based on deep learning techniques, which involves designing a compact representation to encode private and public information, and two neural networks to deal with imperfect information. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper proposes a novel approach to solving a challenging problem in a game using deep learning techniques. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper involves designing and training neural networks to learn bidding strategies. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as the paper deals with a game and proposes a new approach to bidding. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper involves designing a compact representation to encode information. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper involves designing and training neural networks.
